<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1447" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1447">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/143.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guadalajara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Answering your March 5 and 6. Have been protesting against forced loans
                            Americans and other foreigners not having official representation <pb facs="1108" n="992" xml:id="pg_992"/> here and am yet protesting and
                            advising nonpayment except by force. Tried to give you timely
                            information but all my telegrams were suppressed by authorities
                            here.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>